In a shocking incident, our readers have sent us pictures of burnt police Admission of Guilty books in what looks like a cover-up as allegations rise that traffic police are corruptly diverting state fines. ONLINE REPORTERS <img src="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock5-576x1024.jpg" alt="1-roadblock5" width="576" height="1024" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3096224743954630" srcset="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock5-576x1024.jpg 576w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock5-169x300.jpg 169w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock5-56x100.jpg 56w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock5-113x200.jpg 113w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock5.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" />f According to our readers, police officers were manning a roadblock at Mutimurefu, about 20 kilometres from Masvingo along the Mutare highway, using a Ford Fiesta patrol vehicle (Reg ZRP 378R). <img src="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock7-1024x576.jpg" alt="1-roadblock7" width="1024" height="576" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3096224743954632" srcset="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock7-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock7-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock7-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock7-100x56.jpg 100w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock7-200x113.jpg 200w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock7.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /> <img src="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock6-576x1024.jpg" alt="1-roadblock6" width="576" height="1024" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3096224743954631" srcset="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock6-576x1024.jpg 576w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock6-169x300.jpg 169w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock6-56x100.jpg 56w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock6-113x200.jpg 113w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock6.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /> “We were arrested for a faulty registration plate light and they demanded $30 for that defect,  which I thought was too much; we disembarked and…we discovered that there was fire burning. We got interested that we went close to it, and  (we) discovered ticket books being burnt,”said our reader. Our reader said they immediately made efforts to contact police in Harare, who in turn called the Masvingo police. <img src="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock4-576x1024.jpg" alt="1-roadblock4" width="576" height="1024" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3096224743954629" srcset="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock4-576x1024.jpg 576w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock4-169x300.jpg 169w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock4-56x100.jpg 56w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock4-113x200.jpg 113w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/1-roadblock4.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /> “Police in Masvingo phoned me and I told them I had an exhibit and they instructed us to wait for them. We waited, but they (the officers at the roadblock) quickly packed their belongings and drove off without giving us back our driver’s licence discs. It was obvious someone had tipped them.” Our reader said when the Criminal Investigations Department (CID) officers from Masvingo arrived, they followed the roadblock police. “They (CID officers) followed the roadblock police, and returned after an hour.”
